Date: Thu 27 Feb 2003
From: Elena Pedroni <epedroni@msal.gov.ar>
Source: National Coordination for Vector Control, Ministry of Health,
Republic of Argentina, Thu 27 Feb 2003 [translated by Mod.MPP]
[edited]

Argentina: Statement from the Ministry of Health
------------------------------------------------
The National Coordination for Vector Control of the Ministry of
Health of the Republic of Argentina is submitting the following
report with respect to the note posted above, [reproduced from
ProMED-ESP of Mon 24 Feb 2003, see: PRO/ESP> Dengue, serotipo 3,
alerta - Paraguay 20030224.0472], concerning the appearance of dengue
virus serotype 3 in Paraguay and which refers to current cases of
dengue fever in the Argentine provinces of Salta and Misiones. As of
Thu 27 Feb 2003, there have been 2 cases of dengue fever on Argentine
territory: (1) S.S. Jujuy [Health Sector Jujuy], classified as an
imported case from Santa Cruz de la Sierra in Bolivia; and (2) San
Lorenzo (Santa Fe) also classified as an imported case, coming from
Urucui (Mato Grosso, Brazil).
In addition, there are 4 presumptive cases under investigation with
positive IgM results (UM-ELISA and MAC-ELISA) and 35 clinically
suspected cases from Jujuy and Salta. Of the 260 cases that were
referred to [in the above ProMED-mail posting], it is important to
clarify that these cases occurred in 2002, during an outbreak in
Salta due to dengue virus serotype 1 (DEN-1), whereas in Misiones,
during the same period, there was only one case reported, an imported
case of dengue virus serotype 3 (DEN-3) from Brazil.
--
Elena Pedroni
<epedroni@msal.gov.ar>
