Source: El Comercio, Ecuador, AFP report, Sat 21 Feb 2003 [in
Spanish, translated and summarized by Mod.JW]
<http://www.elcomercio.com/noticias.asp?noid=52901>

Ecuador: Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever Total Reaches 24 for 2003
-------------------------------------------------
In total, 24 cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) have now been
reported in Ecuador during 2003, according to statistics released
today by the National Sub-secretariat of Tropical Medicine; 21 of
those cases are from Guayas province.
Last week the first death from DHF was registered, a 13-year-old
child [sex not specified] in Manabi, in the southwest, one of the 12
provinces which have been declared by the government to be in a state
of medical and health emergency [due to dengue].
In 2002, 14 cases of DHF and 6688 of classic dengue fever were reported.
